Compliance Officer Job Responsibilities:
• Provides audit information to management by researching and analyzing data; preparing reports.
• Prepares compliance audit data by compiling and analyzing internal and external information.
• Provides administrative support by implementing systems, procedures, and policies; completing projects in support of compliance auditors.
• Complies with federal, state, and local legal requirements by studying existing and new legislation.
• Enforces adherence to requirements and advises management on needed actions.
• Enhances compliance department and organization reputation by accepting ownership for accomplishing new and different requests
• Review KYC information &amp; documents of clients in accordance to the standards
• Perform AML/CTF risk monitoring on clients and account transactions using the transaction ongoing monitoring tool
Requirements:
• Able to manage time and complete tasks under a tight deadline
• Communicate well and willing to multitask
• Understand KYC/AML/Transaction Monitoring requirements for various client types
• Min. Degree and above
• Min 3 years’ experience in Compliance/AML/KYC related roles
• Able to travel to Asia Region
Basic Salary: $3500 - $4500
Working days: Monday to Friday (Office Hours)
Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.
